@svinota  Did a little deep dive into the nla_map compilation. Was this ever working? Would be striking if not, since heavily used this way. (see my tst script)  Seems all yours. Could you have look?

Allows for e.g.:
```python

@client.async_event
def on_message(message):
    if message.content.startswith('$greet')
        yield from client.send_message(message.channel, 'First one to say hi wins!')
        msg = yield from client.wait_for_message(channel=message.channel, content='hi')
        yield from client.send_message(message.channel, '{} wins!'.format(msg.author.name))
```

This fixes **setup.py** and **tox.ini** according to Issue #10

Prevents PIP from complaining about upgrading requests module every time we want to update both **webpreview** and **requests** modules.

@ludbek in order for this to work, the package must be updated on PyPI.

@spra85 @MichaelButkovic @benghaziboy 

